03:17.531 --> 03:22.203
<i>It was summer,
1948, and I needed money.</i>

03:22.286 --> 03:24.747
<i>After going door-to-door
all daylong,</i>

03:24.830 --> 03:27.374
<i>I was back again at Joppy's Bar,
tryin' to figure out...</i>

03:27.458 --> 03:30.377
<i>where I was gonna go lookin'
for work the next day.</i>

03:30.461 --> 03:34.506
<i>The newspapers was goin' on
and on about the city elections,</i>

03:34.590 --> 03:37.384
<i>like they was really
gonna change somebody's life.</i>

03:37.468 --> 03:41.722
<i>Well, my life had already changed when
I lost my job three weeks before.</i>

03:41.805 --> 03:46.477
For example, one of the white
guys pulls a double shift,

03:46.560 --> 03:50.564
says he's too tired to work
overtime, you don't fire them.

03:50.648 --> 03:52.816
That's all
you have to say?

04:02.243 --> 04:05.037
No, no, that's not all.
I-I need...

04:07.498 --> 04:11.418
I need to pay
my mortgage, and eat.

04:11.502 --> 04:15.839
I need a house to live in. I need to
put clothes on my back, Mr. Giacomo.

04:15.923 --> 04:19.718
- I need the job.
- I'm sorry, fella. I gotta get back to work.

04:22.888 --> 04:25.015
My name's not “fella.”

04:25.099 --> 04:27.017
Huh?

04:27.101 --> 04:31.105
My name's not “fella.”
My name is Ezekiel Rawlins.

04:31.188 --> 04:33.857
Catch you later, Joppy.

04:33.941 --> 04:37.361
Hey, watch the marble!
Damn it! What'd I tell you?

04:42.574 --> 04:45.869
Joppy, how much you think they're
payin' out there at Douglas Aircraft?

04:45.953 --> 04:49.540
I don't know. Don't it say
on the...

05:07.850 --> 05:12.980
Talk to him. Yes, sir.
You can talk to him.

05:13.063 --> 05:16.859
All right.
Easy, come on over here.

05:16.942 --> 05:19.945
I've got somebody
I want you to meet.

05:23.824 --> 05:27.244
Come on. This here's
a friend of mine.

05:27.328 --> 05:29.955
Yeah, Easy,
this is Mr. Albright.

05:30.039 --> 05:31.957
- You can call me Dewitt, Easy.
- How you doin'?

05:32.041 --> 05:35.586
- I'm all right.
- Take a seat, Easy.

05:38.005 --> 05:42.509
Mr. Albright and me
go way back to before the war.

05:42.593 --> 05:44.803
Matter of fact, when I was
still in the fight game.

05:44.887 --> 05:47.014
Mm-hmm.
Ever seen this guy fight?

05:47.097 --> 05:49.350
- No.
- No?

05:49.433 --> 05:52.895
Well, shoot. Every time Joppy
Shag stepped into the ring,

05:52.978 --> 05:57.483
you knew you was gonna see some real
knock-down-drag-out fisticuffs.

05:57.566 --> 05:59.902
- Where you from, Easy?
- Houston.

05:59.985 --> 06:03.781
Mmm, Houston.
That's Joppy's hometown.

06:07.493 --> 06:09.286
So, I hear
you need a job.

06:09.370 --> 06:13.165
Oh, yeah, uh, Easy's
always tryin' to do better.

06:13.248 --> 06:17.211
He's one of the few colored men
around here who owns his own house.

06:17.294 --> 06:20.881
He's payin' the mortgage every
month, just like y'all folks.

06:20.964 --> 06:25.886
Property owner, huh? These big companies
don't give a damn, do they, Easy?

06:25.969 --> 06:28.555
I got out of that racket
a long time ago.

06:28.639 --> 06:33.560
Look, if you do need a job, you drop
by this address... 7:00 tonight.

06:33.644 --> 06:36.438
What kind of work you do?

06:38.690 --> 06:42.277
I do favors.
I do favors for friends.

06:43.654 --> 06:45.531
Drop DY-

06:49.493 --> 06:51.412
Who was that,
Joppy?

06:51.495 --> 06:53.747
Just somebody I know.
Businessman.

06:53.831 --> 06:56.166
- Businessman, huh?
- Yeah, he is.

06:57.918 --> 07:00.170
Ain't nothin'
to worry about.

07:00.254 --> 07:03.424
<i>Now, when somebody
tell me ain't nothin' to worry about,</i>

07:03.507 --> 07:06.218
<i>I usually look down
to see if my fly is open.</i>

07:06.301 --> 07:11.265
<i>But all the way home all I could think
about was a chance to make some money.</i>

07:12.683 --> 07:14.309
<i>I first came out
to Los Angeles...</i>

07:14.393 --> 07:17.521
<i>when I got home
from the war in Europe...</i>

07:17.604 --> 07:20.315
<i>with $300 in my pocket
and the G.I. Bill.</i>

07:20.399 --> 07:23.735
- <i>Like me, a lot of colored folk from
Texas and Louisiana...</i> - Hi, Easy.

07:23.819 --> 07:25.946
<i>Had moved out to California
to get them good jobs...</i>

07:26.029 --> 07:30.701
- <i>...in the shipyards and in the
aircraft companies.</i> - Hey, Willy!

07:30.784 --> 07:33.495
<i>Now, me myself,
I was a machinist.</i>

07:33.579 --> 07:38.542
<i>And the first thing I did when I saved
enough money was to buy me a house.</i>

07:40.669 --> 07:43.464
<i>Man, I loved comin' home
to my house.</i>

07:43.547 --> 07:47.134
<i>I don't know. I guess maybe
I just loved ownin' somethin'.</i>

07:49.887 --> 07:52.097
How ya doin'?

07:57.227 --> 08:00.827
- Ezekiel, I'm gonna knock down some of them
trees in the back. - No, leave my trees alone.

08:00.856 --> 08:03.942
- I aint' gonna take but five...
- Get on!

08:26.590 --> 08:29.801
<i>I was feelin' pretty
desperate that evenin'.</i>

08:29.885 --> 08:32.804
<i>In a week I'd be two months
behind on my mortgage,</i>

08:32.888 --> 08:35.640
<i>and, no, sir, I wasn't
about to lose my house.</i>

08:35.724 --> 08:39.352
<i>But a chill runnin' up the back
of my neck was talkin' to me,</i>

08:39.436 --> 08:42.022
<i>tellin' me I was about to make
a bad decision.</i>

08:42.105 --> 08:44.358
<i>Yeah, Albright made me nervous.</i>

08:44.441 --> 08:47.528
<i>He reminded me of a fella I knew
back in Texas named Mouse.</i>

08:47.611 --> 08:50.572
Drive to the train yard, Easy.
Let's dump this damn thing...

08:50.656 --> 08:53.492
- What did you do, Mouse?
- Just drive this son of a bitch.

08:53.575 --> 08:55.619
<i>What did you do?</i>

09:19.309 --> 09:21.353
So...

09:23.355 --> 09:25.566
want the job?

09:25.649 --> 09:29.194
It depends“.on
what kind of job it is.

09:29.278 --> 09:31.572
I don't wanna get
mixed up in nothin'.

09:31.655 --> 09:34.199
Hmm. Walk out the door
in the morning, Easy,

09:34.283 --> 09:37.202
you're mixed up
in somethin'.

09:37.286 --> 09:41.415
Only thing that matters is if
you're mixed up to the top or not.

09:41.498 --> 09:44.543
I'm just lookin' for somebody.
For a friend.

09:44.626 --> 09:46.920
Daphne Monet.

09:47.004 --> 09:50.882
Fiancée of Todd Carter.
She been gone two weeks.

09:50.966 --> 09:55.137
It upset the poor man so much,
he stopped runnin' for mayor.

09:56.471 --> 09:58.765
I never laid eyes on her.

09:58.849 --> 10:00.767
That's a shame.

10:00.851 --> 10:04.438
See, Daphne has a predilection
for the company of Negroes.

10:04.521 --> 10:07.691
She likes jazz and pigs' feet
and dark meat.

10:07.774 --> 10:09.901
Know what I mean?

10:09.985 --> 10:11.695
Predilection, yeah.

10:12.863 --> 10:14.573
Yeah.

10:15.741 --> 10:17.618
I'd go lookin'
for her myself, but...

10:17.701 --> 10:21.163
I'm not of the right
persuasion, so to speak.

10:21.246 --> 10:24.958
- What do you want from me?
- What do you mean?

10:25.042 --> 10:27.377
What do you want me to do?

10:27.461 --> 10:30.380
Get a location on her.

10:30.464 --> 10:33.133
Mr. Carter wants
to make up with her.

10:33.216 --> 10:37.679
Hundred dollars.
I pay in advance.

10:42.893 --> 10:44.978
Hundred dollars.

10:45.062 --> 10:48.940
And all I got to do
is tell you where she's at?

10:49.024 --> 10:51.234
- That's right.
- And that's all?

10:51.318 --> 10:53.445
That's all.

10:53.528 --> 10:58.075
- You frequent an illegal club on
89th and Central. - Yeah, John's.

10:58.158 --> 11:00.994
Somebody saw Daphne there
a few nights ago.

11:01.078 --> 11:03.205
You could start tonight.

11:10.087 --> 11:11.755
Hmm.

11:17.719 --> 11:21.348
Whoa, that's enough.
Thank you.

11:21.431 --> 11:24.142
See you later, man.
All right. Yeah.

